    <p> The average lead levels in Flint daycares shown above are all at safe levels. The children of Flint have access to cleaner water than they did before. The youth to come will have access to filtered water. This shows a promising future for the youth of Flint.</p>

    <p>Lead levels continue to go down year after year by small increments. However, the damage that was done from the initial crisis is irreversible. The children growing up in Flint now who are going to daycare will have safer levels of water to drink. However, those children who came before them cannot get the years of dirty water back.</p>

 
      <p>Although filtration systems are getting better, the crisis is still ongoing. The filtration systems are working better, but the water itself is still contaminated. Although officials have deemed water lean enough to drink, they still shy against it if there is another option (Strauss, 2019).
</p>

